it to create spirit disasters

249
00:13:31,896 --> 00:13:33,629
and escape in the confusion.

250
00:13:33,662 --> 00:13:37,229
[HIRATA] Good to know. I suppose
there's no going back now.

251
00:13:37,262 --> 00:13:40,296
Right, if even
one or two of us can--

252
00:13:45,396 --> 00:13:46,862
Sorry about this.

253
00:13:46,896 --> 00:13:48,762
[gunshot]

254
00:14:00,896 --> 00:14:02,362
[HIRATA] The Magical
Investigation Bureau

255
00:14:02,396 --> 00:14:05,629
didn't know about
Doman's tool either.

256
00:14:05,662 --> 00:14:08,229
I was right to come take
care of this in person,

257
00:14:08,262 --> 00:14:10,429
take care of you.

258
00:14:10,462 --> 00:14:13,729
The liaison, it's you?

259
00:14:13,762 --> 00:14:15,529
You don't know the whole
truth, but it would be

260
00:14:15,562 --> 00:14:19,729
problematic for you to fall
into the hands of the MIB.

261
00:14:19,762 --> 00:14:21,262
Believe me.

262
00:14:21,296 --> 00:14:23,362
[HIRATA]
I'm sorry, Makihara.

263
00:14:28,862 --> 00:14:31,662
[cell phone beeps]

264
00:14:31,696 --> 00:14:33,796
[HIRATA] It's finished.
However, there will soon be

265
00:14:33,829 --> 00:14:36,762
spirit disasters
in the branch office.

266
00:14:36,796 --> 00:14:38,729
Correct. The Twin
Horn Syndicate

267
00:14:38,762 --> 00:14:40,896
within the agency
has been wiped out.

268
00:14:40,929 --> 00:14:43,129
So Kagami can also--

269
00:14:43,162 --> 00:14:44,396
Yes, I know.

270
00:14:44,429 --> 00:14:46,729
I don't want him
near Kagami either.

271
00:14:48,662 --> 00:14:52,196
[AMAMI] Would you mind giving
the phone to me next, Hirata?

272
00:14:56,329 --> 00:14:57,662
[scoffs]

273
00:14:58,762 --> 00:15:01,329
[HIRATA] I had a feeling
that you were on to me.

274
00:15:01,362 --> 00:15:03,162
When did you realize?

275
00:15:04,862 --> 00:15:07,396
My apologies,
but the only one who's

276
00:15:07,429 --> 00:15:10,362
going to be asking questions
at the moment is me.

277
00:15:10,396 --> 00:15:11,596
[gun hammer clicks]

278
00:15:11,629 --> 00:15:13,662
[AMAMI] Actually, it's been
fascinating watching you work

279
00:15:13,696 --> 00:15:17,329
so aggressively even after
the plan went into effect.

280
00:15:17,362 --> 00:15:20,129
I was so impressed, I almost
felt bad about the fact

281
00:15:20,162 --> 00:15:22,596
that I would
have to call you out.

282
00:15:22,629 --> 00:15:24,496
I was shocked, though.

283
00:15:24,529 --> 00:15:28,196
I didn't think murder
would be so easy for you.

284
00:15:29,429 --> 00:15:31,529
[AMAMI] I believed I had a
pretty good understanding

285
00:15:31,562 --> 00:15:33,896
of Yakou devotees.
But I never would have

286
00:15:33,929 --> 00:15:37,162
imagined there was scum
like you on their side.

287
00:15:38,529 --> 00:15:41,896
Now, calm down and don't
do anything stupid, Hirata.

288
00:15:41,929 --> 00:15:44,529
[HIRATA] I am going
to restrain you.

289
00:15:44,562 --> 00:15:46,629
Is this the part where
you try to brainwash me

290
00:15:46,662 --> 00:15:48,696
into becoming
a Yakou devotee?

291
00:15:48,729 --> 00:15:50,329
If I can welcome
you as a comrade,

292
00:15:50,362 --> 00:15:51,729
it would be worth any risk.

293
00:15:51,762 --> 00:15:54,396
And on top of that,
you'd be quite the catch.

294
00:15:55,929 --> 00:15:58,196
[AMAMI]
I am terribly honored.

295
00:15:58,229 --> 00:16:00,329
[HIRATA] Please,
don't move, Amami.

296
00:16:00,362 --> 00:16:04,162
Let me be clear and say
this one more time, Hirata.

297
00:16:05,229 --> 00:16:08,329
Calm down and
don't do anything stupid.

298
00:16:10,796 --> 00:16:12,329
[groans]

299
00:16:14,162 --> 00:16:15,662
[HIRATA] My movements!

300
00:16:16,462 --> 00:16:17,496
Order!

301
00:16:17,529 --> 00:16:19,296
Oh, don't bother with that.

302
00:16:21,762 --> 00:16:23,829
You should have realized
I wasn't just talking

303
00:16:23,862 --> 00:16:25,862
to hear the sound
of my own voice.

304
00:16:25,896 --> 00:16:28,429
I've already made
the first move, kid.

305
00:16:28,462 --> 00:16:29,829
You should be ashamed.

306
00:16:29,862 --> 00:16:31,796
[HIRATA] Wait.
This is a high-grade spell.

307
00:16:31,829 --> 00:16:33,496
Is this Kagami's?

308
00:16:33,529 --> 00:16:35,329
[AMAMI chuckles]
Give me a break.

309
00:16:35,362 --> 00:16:37,896
A real high-grade spell
is more elegant than that.

310
00:16:37,929 --> 00:16:41,496
It's much more refined
and sophisticated.

311
00:16:41,529 --> 00:16:43,796
A magical form of art.

312
00:16:45,396 --> 00:16:47,662
[HIRATA] A magical tool?
There's probably a spell

313
00:16:47,696 --> 00:16:49,562
on the other side of that fan.

314
00:16:49,596 --> 00:16:51,496
No, there's more
to it than that.

315
00:16:51,529 --> 00:16:52,562
Everything he's said up to now

316
00:16:52,596 --> 00:16:54,896
has to have been
laced with curses.

317
00:16:54,929 --> 00:16:58,596
[AMAMI] What's wrong? Feeling
a little cornered over there?

318
00:16:59,929 --> 00:17:04,396
[AMAMI'S footsteps]

319
00:17:04,429 --> 00:17:06,662
I'm calling for you, now.

320
00:17:12,196 --> 00:17:13,796
You have Defenders?

321
00:17:15,796 --> 00:17:19,329
Servant familiars?
Don't tell me this guy is...

322
00:17:24,296 --> 00:17:26,796
An Imperial
pallbearer? Impossible!

323
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:29,096
[AMAMI] Just what
in the world are you?

324
00:17:31,796 --> 00:17:34,829
[HIRATA'S FAMILIARS roar]

325
00:17:34,862 --> 00:17:37,229
[AMAMI] Arrogant bastard,
aren't you?

326
00:17:37,262 --> 00:17:41,496
Om biro bakisha
nagya jihata ei sowaka!

327
00:17:42,462 --> 00:17:52,462
♪

328
00:17:57,796 --> 00:18:01,796
That man's spirit power
is incredible! Kingi! Gingi!

329
00:18:07,296 --> 00:18:14,829
[AMAMI recites spell]

330
00:18:14,862 --> 00:18:18,162
[AMAMI continues]

331
00:18:50,529 --> 00:18:54,096
One! Two! Three! Order!

332
00:18:57,262 --> 00:18:59,196
Oh, there's no use.

333
00:19:03,529 --> 00:19:05,096
Four!

334
00:19:10,362 --> 00:19:12,662
Heh. How about that?

335
00:19:17,762 --> 00:19:19,429
Stop! That's enough!

336
00:19:22,696 --> 00:19:25,629
[AMAMI] Very impressive
spiritual pressure!

337
00:19:31,218 --> 00:19:34,818
I must know.
What in the world are you?

338
00:19:34,851 --> 00:19:36,818
I am a Yakou devotee.

339
00:19:36,851 --> 00:19:39,385
I am someone who
has inherited his will.

340
00:19:39,418 --> 00:19:41,351
So you don't consider
yourself the same

341
00:19:41,385 --> 00:19:43,018
as the Twin Horn Syndicate?

342
00:19:43,051 --> 00:19:44,718
I am nothing like them.

343
00:19:44,751 --> 00:19:46,218
They genuinely
believe that as long as

344
00:19:46,251 --> 00:19:47,818
Yakou is finally resurrected,

345
00:19:47,851 --> 00:19:50,151
they will receive their
own personal glory.

346
00:19:50,185 --> 00:19:51,385
But they've become
frustrated with

347
00:19:51,418 --> 00:19:54,018
their faith's inability
to produce rewards, yet,

348
00:19:54,051 --> 00:19:56,318
their lack of faith
causes them to blame Yakou.

349
00:19:56,351 --> 00:19:59,018
Those people have
no shame to speak of!

350
00:19:59,051 --> 00:20:00,785
From what I've heard
that's just the kind of

351
00:20:00,818 --> 00:20:03,118
organization the
Twin Horn Syndicate is.

352
00:20:03,151 --> 00:20:05,851
[HIRATA] Wrong! The Syndicate
was an organization

353
00:20:05,885 --> 00:20:09,185
created in order to realize
Yakou's last wishes!

354
00:20:09,218 --> 00:20:10,685
But instead,
they've been reduced to

355
00:20:10,718 --> 00:20:13,885
a group of mindless,
ignorant fanatics.

356
00:20:13,918 --> 00:20:14,751
[AMAMI] Hmmm.

357
00:20:14,785 --> 00:20:16,318
So that must be
the reason you decided

358
00:20:16,351 --> 00:20:18,885
to kill your former
comrades. Right?

359
00:20:18,918 --> 00:20:20,618
[HIRATA] If they wanted
to be the foundation of

360
00:20:20,651 --> 00:20:22,185
the realization
of Yakou's will,

361
00:20:22,218 --> 00:20:24,351
then they should
have been satisfied.

362
00:20:24,385 --> 00:20:25,918
[HIRATA] I regret
the sacrifices that

363
00:20:25,951 --> 00:20:27,618
had to be made this time.

364
00:20:27,651 --> 00:20:29,051
However, I plan
to bear the burden

365
00:20:29,085 --> 00:20:31,118
of these sins personally.

366
00:20:31,151 --> 00:20:33,618
[AMAMI] Isn't that
noble of you.

367
00:20:34,351 --> 00:20:37,351
So tell me, then.
What exactly is the Syndicate

368
00:20:37,385 --> 00:20:40,118
founded on, anyway?
How old is this group?

369
00:20:40,151 --> 00:20:42,118
Is it true the
organization was formed

370
00:20:42,151 --> 00:20:45,018
by contemporaries who were
taught by Yakou himself?

371
00:20:45,051 --> 00:20:46,718
[HIRATA] Those who
follow Yakou's will are

372
00:20:46,751 --> 00:20:48,618
divided into two groups.

373
00:20:48,651 --> 00:20:50,718
One is the
Twin Horn Syndicate.

374
00:20:50,751 --> 00:20:53,618
The other group is
the Onmyo Prep School.

375
00:20:54,285 --> 00:20:56,618
[HIRATA] The Onmyo Prep
School was originally created

376
00:20:56,651 --> 00:20:58,751
by Yakou from his
desire to raise new,

377
00:20:58,785 --> 00:21:01,385
talented Onmyo mages.

378
00:21:01,418 --> 00:21:03,185
In the same vein,
the Twin Horn Syndicate

379
00:21:03,218 --> 00:21:06,285
was formed because
of his other desire.

380
00:21:06,318 --> 00:21:08,018
We are all
students of Yakou,

381
00:21:08,051 --> 00:21:10,618
and we are all here
because of Him.

382
00:21:11,718 --> 00:21:13,785
I understand.

383
00:21:13,818 --> 00:21:15,951
But I'm curious,
what is the other desire

384
00:21:15,985 --> 00:21:17,651
of Yakou's
that you speak of?

385
00:21:17,685 --> 00:21:19,018
What is it you're
trying to accomplish

386
00:21:19,051 --> 00:21:21,951
for your master?

387
00:21:21,985 --> 00:21:25,318
Director Amami,
listen to me carefully.

388
00:21:25,351 --> 00:21:26,518
[gasps]

389
00:21:26,551 --> 00:21:30,918
[HIRATA] Why? Why am I telling
him everything like this?

390
00:21:32,651 --> 00:21:33,551
[HIRATA exhales shakily]

391
00:21:33,585 --> 00:21:37,385
[AMAMI] Hirata?
Look at me. Just tell me.

392
00:21:37,418 --> 00:21:39,951
What is it you're
trying to do?

393
00:21:39,985 --> 00:21:42,151
[HIRATA] The director of
the Onmyo Agency's MIB

394
00:21:42,185 --> 00:21:43,985
has lowered his guard
and is asking me

395
00:21:44,018 --> 00:21:47,085
innocent questions?
This is wrong!

396
00:21:47,118 --> 00:21:48,985
There's something
wrong about it!

397
00:21:49,018 --> 00:21:53,185
[AMAMI] Concentrate.
Please. Talk to me.

398
00:21:53,218 --> 00:21:55,151
[HIRATA] How could
I be so stupid?

399
00:21:55,185 --> 00:21:56,751
This is all a spell!

400
00:21:56,785 --> 00:21:58,251
Restrain him!

401
00:22:00,685 --> 00:22:03,151
[AMAMI] Oh dear,
is that as much as I get?

402
00:22:03,185 --> 00:22:04,318
Did you know
when you're dealing

403
00:22:04,351 --> 00:22:06,285
with a rather
difficult familiar,

404
00:22:06,318 --> 00:22:09,251
it's best to ensnare
its master immediately?

405
00:22:09,285 --> 00:22:10,951
But how? When could
you have done it?

406
00:22:10,985 --> 00:22:13,218
Why worry about
such minor details.

407
00:22:13,251 --> 00:22:15,685
Now would you mind
handing me my fan?

408
00:22:15,718 --> 00:22:17,618
[AMAMI]
It's right behind you.

409
00:22:18,151 --> 00:22:28,151
♪

410
00:22:32,785 --> 00:22:34,818
Divine Fan, Daizen Amami!

411
00:22:34,851 --> 00:22:37,718
No. I've failed.

412
00:22:37,751 --> 00:22:40,118
Don't worry about that.

413
00:22:40,151 --> 00:22:42,118
[AMAMI] You did
pretty well, kid.

414
00:22:44,885 --> 00:22:46,218
[thud]

415
00:22:47,151 --> 00:22:49,618
I told you at the very
beginning, didn't I?

416
00:22:49,651 --> 00:22:50,751
The only one
who's going to be

417
00:22:50,785 --> 00:22:53,285
asking questions here is me.

418
00:22:55,218 --> 00:22:58,185
Those Imperial Pallbearers
had me going for a while.

419
00:22:58,218 --> 00:23:01,118
This was more of a headache
than I imagined it would be.

420
00:23:05,785 --> 00:23:07,318
[AMAMI gasps lightly]

421
00:23:07,351 --> 00:23:10,151
What? There's no way.

422
00:23:14,918 --> 00:23:17,051
You've gotta be kidding me.

423
00:23:17,085 --> 00:23:19,285
What the hell is going on?

424
00:23:21,185 --> 00:23:23,085
[HARUTORA] Even if class is
over, it doesn't mean that

425
00:23:23,118 --> 00:23:25,218
they're done hunting
the Twin Horn Syndicate.

426
00:23:25,251 --> 00:23:26,151
I think we should
stick together

427
00:23:26,185 --> 00:23:28,718
as much as possible.
Touji and Tenma are

428
00:23:28,751 --> 00:23:31,051
looking for Suzuka,
so she can join us.

429
00:23:31,085 --> 00:23:33,051
[ETOU] What are you doing?

430
00:23:33,085 --> 00:23:35,285
How can you just
waste our time?

431
00:23:35,318 --> 00:23:38,618
[ETOU] There are people fighting
desperately on your behalf.

432
00:23:38,651 --> 00:23:40,318
I'm not sure what
you're talking about.

433
00:23:40,351 --> 00:23:42,818
Does this mean you're not
going to help them, then?

434
00:23:42,851 --> 00:23:44,385
Are those stupid
believers' simply

435
00:23:44,418 --> 00:23:46,718
insignificant beings
that are beneath you?

436
00:23:46,751 --> 00:23:49,151
Too worthless
for you to notice?

437
00:23:49,185 --> 00:23:51,985
Please, enlighten me,
King of the North Star.

438
00:23:52,018 --> 00:23:52,885
[NATSUME and KYOKO gasp]

439
00:23:52,918 --> 00:23:54,851
The Twin Horn Syndicate?

440
00:23:55,751 --> 00:24:00,151
Boring, boring, boring,
boring, so boring.

441
00:24:00,185 --> 00:24:02,651
[KON] Let Master Harutora
have more to do next week,

442
00:24:02,685 --> 00:24:03,785
please and thank you.

